						<summary>

						<p>Wall of the Bhairavēśvara temple in survey No. 274.</p>						

						<p>This is dated <hi rend="bold">Śaka 1440, Bahudhānya, Āshāḍha śu. 12, Sunday</hi> corresponding to 1518 A.D. June 20.</p>						

						<p>It records the grant of land as <hi rend="italic">Polamēramānya</hi> made by <hi rend="italic">asēshavidvan-mahājanas</hi> of Pushpagiri to Mummaḍi-reḍḍi of Gōṁṭūru for having marked out the boundaries between the villages Gōṁṭūru and Chernūru.</p>						

						</summary>
